  <main id="main">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="wrap">
        <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
        <h1>From one application to suitable work allocation.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Cleaning Jobs gives suitable cleaners a single, structured pathway into Spruce-standard cleaning work. Here&rsquo;s what each stage involves.</p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apply/">Apply now <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a>
          <a class="btn btn-outline" href="/faq/">Read the FAQ</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block tint">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="why-split">
          <div class="why-left">
            <span class="eyebrow">The pathway</span>
            <h2>Five clear stages.</h2>
            <p>One application is reviewed once. Suitable applicants then move through onboarding, training, and standards before any work is considered, so you always know what stage you&rsquo;re at.</p>
            <p>Work is never guaranteed. Allocation depends on demand, suitability, availability, and certification.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="why-panel">
            <div class="why-rows">
              <div class="why-row"><span class="n">01</span><div><h3>Apply online</h3><p>One short application. Tell us your location, experience, transport, and the cleaning work you&rsquo;re suited for. It takes a few minutes.</p></div></div>
              <div class="why-row"><span class="n">02</span><div><h3>We review your application</h3><p>Every application is reviewed individually against current demand and suitability. We&rsquo;ll contact you if there&rsquo;s a suitable next step.</p></div></div>
              <div class="why-row"><span class="n">03</span><div><h3>Complete verification</h3><p>Right-to-work confirmation and basic checks, completed once as part of onboarding.</p></div></div>
              <div class="why-row"><span class="n">04</span><div><h3>Train or certify to the Spruce standard</h3><p>Short onboarding and role-based training or assessment against the Spruce standard, using the same checklists and expectations used across the network.</p></div></div>
              <div class="why-row"><span class="n">05</span><div><h3>Eligible for suitable work allocation</h3><p>Once certified, you&rsquo;re considered for suitable work based on location, demand, availability, and certification.</p></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="reliable-split">
          <div class="reliable-left">
            <span class="eyebrow">Before you apply</span>
            <h2>What you&rsquo;ll need.</h2>
            <p class="callout">Most of this is confirmed during onboarding.</p>
            <p>You don&rsquo;t need everything ready to apply, but these help, and we&rsquo;ll ask about your situation in the application.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="tick-panel">
            <div class="tick-list">
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">The right to work in New Zealand</span></div>
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">A contactable phone number and email</span></div>
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">Reliable transport for many residential areas</span></div>
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">Basic equipment for some residential work</span></div>
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">Willingness to follow checklists</span></div>
              <div class="tick-row"><span class="check" aria-hidden="true"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><path d="M5 12l4 4 10-10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span><span class="lbl">Comfort with active, practical work</span></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block tint">
      <div class="wrap">
        <div class="sec-head">
          <span class="eyebrow">After you&rsquo;re eligible</span>
          <h2>How work is allocated</h2>
          <p>Being eligible means you&rsquo;re considered for suitable work, not that work is guaranteed. The mix and amount of work depend on what&rsquo;s happening in your area.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="types-note">
          Work is not guaranteed. Allocation depends on demand, suitability, availability, and certification, and the available work types vary by location.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-band" id="apply-cta">
